originalText.text:
In NYC you can find better. I just went to get my gel polish taken off and the whole time they tried to up sell me. THE WHOLE TIME. I speak Chinese and the whole time the entire staff was just talking about upselling their customers and how mad and annoyed they were they people didn’t want to pay more for things and then said they would intentionally do a okay/bad job (taking less time, rushing and trying to get them to pay fast and leave immediately

Honestly just go somewhere else. It’s such a bad environment.

originalText.text: Great ambiance and cleanliness. I paid $100 for a gel mani & regular pedi. Unfortunately, I wouldn’t say that the price reflects the quality of service. My manicure is a tiny bit splotchy and there is build up around my cuticles. My toenail polish started peeling once I left. They fixed it quickly once I came back though.

originalText.text:
Not that great experience today.  I wanted a manicure & pedicure just to try it out did not go for anything extravaganza.

Anyhow, didn't really feel that great. I felt rushed with my pedicure was not busy so i dont know why she was rushing and whilst in the middle of my manicure treatment after finishing my pedicure which was disappointing  I was asked to pay and was then told by the lady doing my manicure 'she preferred getting tip in cash'. I could not understand her well due to the face mask and possibly her talking too fast.

I was a little taken back by it due to:-
1. I have not even finished my manicure
2. She is asking me to pay
3. Demanding that her tip is in cash (firstly I was carrying no cash and was planning on paying on my card and was still in the middle of my manicure).

Really bad service and was not happy at all. I came here to feel relaxed & walked away feeling stressed and disappointed on the attitude. More Importantly they should be making customers feel at ease but it came across not genuine. I even felt they were trying to sell me one level up manicure & pedicure which I wasn't interested in.

The only good thing I found was that whilst drying my nails my thumb nail polish came off and she was polite to do it again, but I still feel it is a bit of a money waste to be honest.

I was polite on my way out as i did not want to spoil my day as I feel all they cared about is a tip or like reminding me I must pay the tip.  Anyhow, will not be going back ridiculous.

originalText.text: I’ve been here twice and have really loved the results both times! I get a gel manicure every three weeks and had to find a new place once moving to the area. The technicians I had were Amy and CiCi, and I highly recommend both as they are meticulous. Making this place my new regular, thank you!

originalText.text: Both times the manicurist told me my toes were dry and both times she was wrong! It wasn't crowded so I don't know what the rush was. It's very clean and serene but then so is my house so I didn't go there for that. I went there for a professional manicure/pedicure and paid a lot--expected much more than I got. And the fingernail polish started chipping off my natural nails after one day. Normally I would have given an even lower rating but the manager did offer to redo. But who has time for that? Disappointed.
